column5: Count me in !!!
Drove by the Final Score about 12:15 PM today on my way home from purchasing a new Laptop.....it almost beckoned to me to come in for a brontie but I fought the temptation
I deliberately avoid that area around lunchtime - I don't have that much willpower! -Brian
Yeah good thing for you they have limited truck parking and your 'lunch time' is about 11pm!  jjcanoe
Looks like I won't make it this time guys. Sorry but something has came up. See ya at the next one.
Only 52 minutes more until the swill!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!   jjcanoe
Only 51 minutes until the Swill!!!!!!  jjcanoe
I'll be at your place for 6:50
10-4!!!!!!  Only 26 minutes until the swill!!!!!!!!!  jjcanoe
Had a great time !!! It was nice meeting up with some of the London members and chowin down some wings.Lookin forward to our next London G2G....  Cheers !!!
OK, glad y'all had a good time. Now where are the pics??
Roy,beleive it or not......everyone forgot their cameras at home last night...Geeeeeezzzzz !!!!!!
....No pictures, man that's sucks! Good to hear you had a good time though but sheeeesh we need pictures.
No pictures is a good thing. Studd danced nekkid on the table dressed only in the hot sauce that dripped off his wings. The world isn't ready for that sight.  JF
My eyes are still hurting from that one!!  Great to meet all you guys again. Fun was had by all, hope everyone made it home safe and we'll be looking forward to the next one!!!  jjcanoe
I snuck in just ahead of the blow. This morning I spieled the driveway for the first time this winter.  JF
Wasn't going to shovel today since it's supposed to rain and get warm today but the weather channel says it all might freeze solid overnight.  D'oh!   jjcanoe
Great time last night. Waiting for the next one.  Rick
Sorry. I'm new at this. I didn't know the code. Good thing I didn't tell what Rick & Brian did then, huh?  JF
Shortly speaking : IT DID NOT HAPPEN

LONDON SWILL - Saturday Dec. 1 2007 - 7PM - FINAL SCORE  Final Score Bar & Grill 850 Wharncliffe Road South 519 686-7500  Click for map  Terry has offered us half price wings and a discount on draught pitchers in anticipation of 20 people attending.  Leafs vs. Penguins on the tube! Spouses welcome!
Thanks for doing the leg work for us. Make sure to give us a reminder that week, I have a great memory it's just very short.
Would we have to sit near that sorry looking lot? I'd be worried about losing my beer, or my food.  JF
hi all will be in attendence cheers jamie
Looks good to me.
Losing your beer and food should be the least of your worries... I haven't been the same since last year's hazing ritual.   Cool!
Lets see leave the bar head up steelheading after on Lake Huron..... that might work for me.

well here I thought COOL I will make the next swill at the fishing show but I am not able to show for this one the belle river chapter has our Christmas dinner that night have a good one all we will have some pops for ya down here

Thats a bummer Mike! There seemed to be enough interest for a swill before Christmas AND during the London something,something and fishing show so you won't have to wait another year for a swill... just until February. -Brian
Okay. Long as the're going after yer beer and not mine.  JF
Mebbe to be safe I should drink Carlings?  JF
Is there any chance we could get this thread pinned?
Should be able to attend this one.  Had lots of fun at the last one!  Just have to line up my designated driver!  jjcanoe

I'll volunteer, provided it's not miles outa my way, and provided it's not an all-nighter. I have to drive home to Stratford afterwards so I can go either east or north outa town. Komoka is not on the itinerary though.  JF

John I might take you up on that offer. I'm on your way & I certainly know the way. But than you just might "have to sit near some of the sorry looking lot". My Packer hat can't miss a swill.  Best Wishes: Rick
Great. Hey, if yer old enuf (hard to tell age with the facial fuzz), we might have played football together in St.Marys. Or are you a london school boy?  JF

St.Thomas School boy (Last 2 years of HS anyways both @ Voden and Parkside) here... as well as a Mustang.. grew up in Mount hope though...It is a long story... to make a long story short... I fended for myself at 16 on...  Paid for my schooling myself as well.. working while going to school to pay the rent and my tuition  Go 'Stangs!  PS... is the Spoke still alive and kicking... man I miss the drunken antics of that place!! saw ALOT of firsts there..  G.
Actually started school in London but went to junior high & high school in Stratford. Finished high school in 78.  Rick
Sheesh. Yer just a pup.  JF

Hey Gerritt...I'm a Western Grad (1992) as well...although I was about as far away from athletics as one can get.  I'm not sure if the Spoke is still there....but I was in a band that played there from time to time.  Great memories of that place!  Also used to frequent the Elbow Room in UCC....I heard that's gone now....
And according to the wife "barely house broken & not that well trained either".   :blahblah1:
Real men can't be trained. Eructation & flatulence were invented so we could assert that independence.  JF
Damn that explains things. I'm independent. Although I expect she will say "way too often".
That doesn't mean it okay to stink up the car.  JF
I'll be there, sound like good times!
